content:
The following article provides steps to install Nginx Proxy Manager LXC (Linux Container) in Proxmox, using &ldquo;Advanced&rdquo; installation options.
Installation can be done, using Proxmox VE Helper-Scripts
Warning: Before executing any scripts on the server, it&rsquo;s strongly recommended that you review them.
Installation steps Go to the Proxmox shell and execute the following command:
bash -c &#34;$(wget -qLO - https://github.com/tteck/Proxmox/raw/main/ct/nginxproxymanager.sh)&#34; This command will launch the installation wizard:
This will create a New Nginx Proxy Manager LXC. Proceed? Select &lt;Yes&gt;
Use Default Settings? Select &lt;Advanced&gt;
To make a selection, use the spacebar. Select &lt;Ok&gt;
Debian 12. If the default Linux distribution is not adhered to, script support will be discontinued. Select &lt;Ok&gt;
Choose Distribution Select (*) debian and &lt;Ok&gt;
Choose Version Select (*) 12 Bookworm and &lt;Ok&gt;
Choose Type Select (*) 1 Unprivileged and &lt;Ok&gt;
Set Root Password (needed for root ssh access) Provide (create) password for root user
Set Container ID Provide container ID. This is a (non-existing) numeric value to identify a container or virtual machine. In this example, we set ID to 2000
Set Hostname In this example our hostname is nginx-proxman, set the name and select &lt;Ok&gt;
Set Disk Size in GB In this example, we can keep the default value, 4 GB and press &lt;Ok&gt;
Allocate CPU Cores We can keep the default value of 2 and press &lt;Ok&gt;
Allocate RAM in MiB By default, the selected value is 1 GB (or 1024 MiB). In this example, we will set the value to 2 GB (or 2048 MiB)
Set a Bridge This will select the network interface. In this example, our network interface is vmbr1 (test network: 10.10.20.0/24)
Set a Static IPv4 CIDR Address (/24) Set static IP for this LXC: 10.10.20.10/24
Enter gateway IP address Gateway IP in our test network is 10.10.20.1
Set APT-Cacher IP (leave blank for default) Use default value (leave it blank) and select &lt;Ok&gt;
Disable IPv6? Disable IPv6 by selecting &lt;Yes&gt;
Set Interface MTU size (leave blank for default) Use default value (leave it blank) and select &lt;Ok&gt;
Set a DNS Search Domain (leave blank for HOST) Use default value (leave it blank) and select &lt;Ok&gt;
Set a DNS Server IP (leave blank for HOST) In this example, Google DNS server 8.8.8.8 is used
Set a MAC Address (leave blank for default) Use default value (leave it blank) and select &lt;Ok&gt;
Set a Vlan (leave blank for default) Use default value (leave it blank) and select &lt;Ok&gt;
Enable Root SSH Access? In this example configuration, we do not enable Root SSH access. Select &lt;No&gt;.
Note: If you want to enable Root SSH access, select &lt;Yes&gt;
Enable Verbose Mode? In this example configuration, we disable verbose mode. Select &lt;No&gt;
Ready to create Nginx Proxy Manager LXC? Finally, select &lt;Yes&gt; to create the container.
Which storage pool you would like to use for the container template? To make a selection, use the Spacebar. Select the storage pool, where the container template is stored. In this example, select vm-storage and press &lt;Ok&gt;
Which storage pool you would like to use for the container? To make a selection, use the Spacebar. Select the storage pool, where the container is stored. In this example, select vm-storage and press &lt;Ok&gt;
Complete installation process References Proxmox VE Helper-Scripts Github - tteck/Proxmox
